Job Description:
Are you ready to use your data analysis skills at a company where they will truly have an impact? MarginEdge is seeking a talented Data Analyst to join our team and make a significant impact on our rapidly growing data-driven business. This is not your typical data analyst role; it's an exciting opportunity to shape the future of our company through data-driven insights and innovation.As a Data Analyst at MarginEdge, you will be crucial in producing and delivering data products that drive critical business decisions. You'll use tools like Preset and Tableau to unlock the potential of our rapidly growing data sets, uncover hidden trends, and transform raw information into actionable insights. Your work will extend beyond the confines of your desk as you collaborate closely with executive leadership and represent your findings to the entire company.
Imagine the satisfaction of knowing that your analysis and visualizations directly influence strategic decisions made by our top leaders. You'll have the opportunity to interact regularly with our executive team, presenting your insights and recommendations and contributing to the overall growth and success of the organization. Your expertise will be valued, and your contributions will have a tangible impact on the company's trajectory.
This role reports to our Vice President of Data Science and will be supported by our larger Data Science and Software Engineering teams.
MarginEdge: &nbsp;Where hospitality meets technology &nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;
As a team built by former (and current!) restaurant operators, our mission is to bring operators the same energy, attention to detail, and passion that they bring to their guests. Our culture is deeply rooted in service, partially because that’s where so many of our team come from (including everyone on our Business Development team), but also because we believe it is just the right way to run a business. We design our software with profound empathy for the complexity of running a restaurant, and the goal of making the magic just a little easier for operators by taking the complex (read: very annoying) back office tasks off their plate, while empowering them with real-time data.&nbsp;
Our founders share a deep history in both owning and operating restaurants and in building successful tech companies. We are venture-backed and serve 4,400+ restaurants across the US and Canada.
We enable restaurants to make magic while knowing we are doing the same for them. &nbsp;
Essential Functions / Responsibilities
Use our reporting infrastructure and data warehouse to curate data, build reports, and analyze data for trends and patterns important to support the company's daily operations. &nbsp;
Help determine and document the meaning behind our standard vocabulary at the company and ensure there is only one correct answer to any given question. &nbsp;If someone speaks about churn or revenue growth we need to all mean the same thing and have one authoritative place to go for the answer.
Learn everything about the MarginEdge data model. &nbsp;Guide the development of a data model that will support reporting on strategic initiatives for the company. Be an active participant in our code review process for reports. &nbsp;
Respond to feedback from others and provide a quality check on reports built by other teams at the company.&nbsp;
Collaborate closely with executive leadership, offering strategic insights and recommendations to drive key business decisions.
Qualifications
3+ years of experience in data analysis or business intelligence field
Bachelor’s degree in statistics, mathematics, management, or business analytics program is preferred
Proficient in SQL
Experience with Tableau, Preset, or other modern business intelligence/reporting platforms
Some capability in R or Python for data analysis is a plus
Strong communication skills, with the ability to effectively present complex data to non-technical stakeholders.
Strong problem-solving skills and a passion for finding patterns and trends within data.
Experience using Salesforce for reporting or analysis would be a bonus
